data.name: DEXTRACTOR

evidence: "The Dextractor commands allow one to pull exactly and only the information needed for assembly and reconstruction from the source HDF5 files produced by the PacBio RS II sequencer" (end-user command-line tools for analysis).
Multiple CLI tools are described (dextract, dexta/undexta, dexar/undexar, dexqv/undexqv, dex2DB) with usage examples, indicating they are run directly by users rather than imported as a library.
"To compile the programs you must have the HDF5 library installed on your system" â€“ implies users obtain and build from source; no mention of package managers, containers, or binaries.
